msgstr "Initialiser un catalogue depuis le template :"

#: ../../i18n.rst:81 f822dca3ec4b4b98a4709990dab8ff7f
msgid "Then expose the new locale in ``website/web/__init__.py``:"
msgstr "Puis exposer la nouvelle locale dans ``website/web/__init__.py`` :"

#: ../../i18n.rst:87 00a966acada745ed95127449f2521cea
msgid ""
"and add a translation for the language name in the switcher "
"(``base.html``)."
msgstr ""
"et ajouter la traduction du nom de la langue dans le switcher "
"(``base.html``)."

#: ../../i18n.rst:90 25e84a8be6c74709aeb2b8607ef6db8c
msgid "Compiling"
msgstr "Compiler"

#: ../../i18n.rst:92 caeadd92682549af91a73af2744ad099
msgid "Before running the app, compile ``.po`` → ``.mo``:"
msgstr "Avant de lancer l'application, compiler ``.po`` → ``.mo`` :"

#: ../../i18n.rst:99 688ece4067f54165b74eddb3a9b46b6d
msgid "Escaping ``%`` signs"
msgstr "Échapper les ``%``"

#: ../../i18n.rst:101 9ebd4adba90843e0bb91181fc972319a
#, python-format
msgid ""
"Flask-Babel / gettext uses Python's ``%``-formatting. Any literal percent"
" sign in a translatable string must be escaped as ``%%``. This is why "
"``Normalize (%%)`` appears in the templates rather than ``Normalize "
"(%)``. Failing to escape leads to ``ValueError: unsupported format "
"character`` at render time."
msgstr ""
"Flask-Babel / gettext utilisent le format ``%`` de Python. Tout signe "
"pourcent littéral dans une chaîne traduisible doit être échappé en "
"``%%``. C'est pour cela que ``Normalize (%%)`` apparaît dans les "
"templates plutôt que ``Normalize (%)``. Oublier l'échappement provoque "
"``ValueError: unsupported format character`` au rendu."

#: ../../i18n.rst:108 9aaf58fe92a94c7cb5c3f000ad19177b
msgid "Plural forms"
msgstr "Formes plurielles"

#: ../../i18n.rst:110 5600cfec928149968efbf08a5940bafa
msgid "Use ``ngettext`` (aliased as ``_()`` won't work for plurals):"
msgstr "Utiliser ``ngettext`` (l'alias ``_()`` ne marche pas pour les pluriels) :"

#: ../../i18n.rst:116 bdbb99122a98447ab1a1a2f5808fa719
msgid ""
"In the catalogue this yields ``msgid_plural`` and ``msgstr[0] / "
"msgstr[1]`` entries."
msgstr ""
"Dans le catalogue cela produit des entrées ``msgid_plural`` et "
"``msgstr[0] / msgstr[1]``."

#: ../../i18n.rst:119 e5befb54c20b4393a655a1c96b451827
msgid "Translating the documentation itself"
msgstr "Traduire la documentation elle-même"

#: ../../i18n.rst:121 a2674d62347f496cafc31d8ff2f1ecfe
msgid ""
"The RansomLook documentation you are reading now is available in several "
"languages as well. Diagrams use neutral English labels; only the "
"surrounding prose is translated."
msgstr ""
"La documentation RansomLook que vous lisez est elle aussi disponible en "
"plusieurs langues. Les diagrammes utilisent des labels en anglais neutres"
" ; seule la prose qui les entoure est traduite."

#: ../../i18n.rst:126 118ae1fd9bb549f1875968cb729539b8
msgid "Local setup"
msgstr "Configuration locale"

#: ../../i18n.rst:128 95d2657e5f804a84bb6ffb82a240d950
msgid ""
"The extensions required to build a translated documentation are listed in"
" ``docs/requirements.txt`` (``sphinx-intl``). ``conf.py`` already exposes"
" the language through the ``SPHINX_LANGUAGE`` environment variable and "
"points Sphinx at ``docs/locale/`` for translation catalogues."
msgstr ""
"Les extensions nécessaires pour construire une documentation traduite "
"sont listées dans ``docs/requirements.txt`` (``sphinx-intl``). "
"``conf.py`` expose déjà la langue via la variable d'environnement "
"``SPHINX_LANGUAGE`` et pointe Sphinx vers ``docs/locale/`` pour les "
"catalogues."

#: ../../i18n.rst:134 cbfa9b35748540579a41e81b193dcb75
msgid "Extract and update catalogues"
msgstr "Extraire et mettre à jour les catalogues"

#: ../../i18n.rst:136 e4a0cc8eacb94065a22696b0397d2207
msgid "From the repository root:"
msgstr "Depuis la racine du dépôt :"

#: ../../i18n.rst:146 c0a2df7d90f346198785779545d55d14
msgid ""
"Edit the ``docs/locale/fr/LC_MESSAGES/*.po`` files. Any PO editor works "
"(Poedit, VS Code gettext, …)."
msgstr ""
"Éditez les fichiers ``docs/locale/fr/LC_MESSAGES/*.po``. N'importe quel "
"éditeur PO fonctionne (Poedit, VS Code gettext, …)."

#: ../../i18n.rst:150 0c3cfc775c7e4960b6c2223d1232a810
msgid "Build a localised version"
msgstr "Builder une version localisée"

#: ../../i18n.rst:160 3a1d4669b6814f9ba56a51043ad89001
msgid "No compilation step is needed for ``.mo`` — Sphinx reads ``.po`` directly."
msgstr ""
"Aucune étape de compilation pour ``.mo`` — Sphinx lit directement les "
"``.po``."

#: ../../i18n.rst:163 981e78367bcf409496e53b4031a96baf
msgid "Wiring it up on Read the Docs"
msgstr "Câblage sur Read the Docs"

#: ../../i18n.rst:165 0e13e66d9d984d179d078d5e8257be88
msgid ""
"Read the Docs has native support for `documentation translations "
"<https://docs.readthedocs.com/platform/stable/localization.html>`_. The "
"canonical setup is:"
msgstr ""
"Read the Docs prend nativement en charge les `traductions de "
"documentation "
"<https://docs.readthedocs.com/platform/stable/localization.html>`_. La "
"configuration canonique est :"

#: ../../i18n.rst:169 0e33e30aba2140e09ce6b0544d88a473
msgid ""
"**Keep a single Git repository** (this one) hosting both the source files"
" and the ``docs/locale/<lang>/`` catalogues."
msgstr ""
"**Gardez un seul dépôt Git** (celui-ci) hébergeant à la fois les fichiers"
" source et les catalogues ``docs/locale/<lang>/``."

#: ../../i18n.rst:171 22fddc63cc58447f93094c5829b493e0
msgid ""
"**Create a \"translation\" project on RTD** for each language (e.g. "
"``ransomlook-fr``). Point it at the same Git repository and branch."
msgstr ""
"**Créez un projet \"translation\" sur RTD** pour chaque langue (ex. "
"``ransomlook-fr``). Faites-le pointer sur le même dépôt Git et la même "
"branche."

#: ../../i18n.rst:173 60c20cfc485b4d79a4feaa18c35e367c
msgid ""
"In the project's *Admin → Advanced settings*, set the **Language** to the"
" target locale (``French``)."
msgstr ""
"Dans *Admin → Advanced settings* du projet, réglez **Language** sur la "
"locale cible (``French``)."

#: ../../i18n.rst:175 5e1b97c85922416ba8d39fdbc35bcab1
msgid ""
"In the project's *Admin → Environment variables*, add "
"``SPHINX_LANGUAGE=fr`` so the build uses the French catalogue."
msgstr ""
"Dans *Admin → Environment variables* du projet, ajoutez "
"``SPHINX_LANGUAGE=fr`` pour que le build utilise le catalogue français."

#: ../../i18n.rst:177 1396cc8fdc4749c99ab397c5599afbf5
msgid ""
"Open the **main** project (English). Go to *Admin → Translations* and "
"**link the French project** as a translation. Read the Docs will then "
"serve the docs at:"
msgstr ""
"Ouvrez le projet **principal** (anglais). Allez dans *Admin → "
"Translations* et **liez le projet français** comme traduction. Read the "
"Docs servira alors les docs à :"

#: ../../i18n.rst:181 38ed7ce3d30a4900ac793bcbbadac086
msgid "``https://ransomlook.readthedocs.io/en/latest/`` (main, default)"
msgstr "``https://ransomlook.readthedocs.io/en/latest/`` (principal, par défaut)"

#: ../../i18n.rst:182 3ef413a7904c4a4a8f4dc127d582bdba
msgid "``https://ransomlook.readthedocs.io/fr/latest/`` (translated)"
msgstr "``https://ransomlook.readthedocs.io/fr/latest/`` (traduit)"

#: ../../i18n.rst:184 a06320c3009e4ef5b27c9c9eef709eb6
msgid "The language switcher in the RTD flyout menu picks this up automatically."
msgstr "Le sélecteur de langue du menu flyout RTD le détecte automatiquement."

#: ../../i18n.rst:186 53360f2cdbbf466b98800a85680aadac
msgid "Repeat steps 2–5 per additional language."
msgstr "Répétez les étapes 2-5 pour chaque langue supplémentaire."

#: ../../i18n.rst:189 7c421e3b0c4e433c894d0279cfa3b4d1
msgid "Keeping translations in sync"
msgstr "Maintenir les traductions à jour"

#: ../../i18n.rst:191 147c9a356e6b4ee98c022fbbd1469347
msgid "Whenever a ``.rst`` file is modified:"
msgstr "À chaque modification d'un fichier ``.rst`` :"

#: ../../i18n.rst:193 c96a6aa08069441aaf92ccd0bca13483
msgid "Re-run ``sphinx-build -b gettext``."
msgstr "Relancer ``sphinx-build -b gettext``."

#: ../../i18n.rst:194 1a444c2ec7f64afe97be9caee4dca5ac
msgid ""
"Re-run ``sphinx-intl update`` — new or changed paragraphs show up as "
"empty or fuzzy entries in the ``.po`` files."
msgstr ""
"Relancer ``sphinx-intl update`` — les paragraphes nouveaux ou modifiés "
"apparaissent vides ou flaggés fuzzy dans les ``.po``."

#: ../../i18n.rst:196 244e436a22254201b4f3db8be27cfbea
msgid "Translate and commit."
msgstr "Traduire et commiter."

#: ../../i18n.rst:198 10a1eac33d814d1cbe924040e74a2488
msgid ""
"Mermaid diagrams use English labels by convention, so they require no "
"translation work. If a diagram ever needs to carry localised text, drop "
"the label into the surrounding prose (which is translated) rather than "
"inside the diagram body."
msgstr ""
"Les diagrammes Mermaid utilisent par convention des labels anglais, "
"aucune traduction n'est donc requise. Si un diagramme doit porter un "
"texte localisé, déplacez-le dans la prose environnante (qui est traduite)"
" plutôt que dans le corps du diagramme."

